# How to install JMeter on Mac


## Getting Started

These instructions will provide step-by-step guideline on how to set up JMeter on Mac.

## Prerequisites

```
•	Java (Requires Java 8+)
```

## Steps

1.	Download .tgz binary file from the link below:

http://jmeter.apache.org/download_jmeter.cgi?src=www.discoversdk.com

2.	Extract the .tgz file and move the folder to any location that you want (eg. “Project” folder).

3.	Open terminal and go to the bin directory of the JMeter folder:

```
$ cd projects/apache-jmeter-5.2.1/bin
```

4. Run jmeter.sh file:

```
$ sh jmeter.sh
```
